<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" ><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="3.9.4">Jekyll</generator><link href="https://dorabiro.github.io/unideb.playgnd/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><link href="https://dorabiro.github.io/unideb.playgnd/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><updated>2024-02-09T15:23:32+01:00</updated><id>https://dorabiro.github.io/unideb.playgnd/feed.xml</id><title type="html">UnidebPlayGnd</title><subtitle>Debreceni Egyetem</subtitle><entry><title type="html">Sallen-Key Filter</title><link href="https://dorabiro.github.io/unideb.playgnd/jekyll/update/2024/02/08/welcome-to-jekyll.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Sallen-Key Filter" /><published>2024-02-08T17:28:23+01:00</published><updated>2024-02-08T17:28:23+01:00</updated><id>https://dorabiro.github.io/unideb.playgnd/jekyll/update/2024/02/08/welcome-to-jekyll</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://dorabiro.github.io/unideb.playgnd/jekyll/update/2024/02/08/welcome-to-jekyll.html"><![CDATA[<p>In this post you can read about a special case of the general <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki Sallen%E2%80%93Key_topology">Sallen-Key</a> topology, where equal resistor and capacitor values were used:  <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">R1 = R2 = R</code> and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">C1 = C2 = C</code>. In the following you can find the tools, results, and methods which I used.</p>

<p>Used instruments:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Oscilloscope RIGOL DS1074 Z+</li>
  <li>Function generator RIGOL DG1032Z</li>
  <li>Power supply GWInstek GPD3303S</li>
</ul>

<p>Used components:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>U1 = LM358
U2 = OP482
R1 = R2 = R4 = R5 = 10kΩ
R3 = 1kΩ
C1 = C2 = 10nF
C3 = C4 = 47uF
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Measurement parameters:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>Frequency range: 10 Hz - 10 kHz
Signal waveform: sinusoidal
Output signal level: 5 Vpp
IC supply voltage: ±12 V
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Used software and packages:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>KiCAD
LTSpice
SciLab
Python PyVISA-Py"
</code></pre></div></div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="jekyll" /><category term="update" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[In this post you can read about a special case of the general Sallen-Key topology, where equal resistor and capacitor values were used: R1 = R2 = R and C1 = C2 = C. In the following you can find the tools, results, and methods which I used.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Sample</title><link href="https://dorabiro.github.io/unideb.playgnd/jekyll/update/2024/02/01/sample.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Sample" /><published>2024-02-01T00:00:00+01:00</published><updated>2024-02-01T00:00:00+01:00</updated><id>https://dorabiro.github.io/unideb.playgnd/jekyll/update/2024/02/01/sample</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://dorabiro.github.io/unideb.playgnd/jekyll/update/2024/02/01/sample.html"><![CDATA[<p><img src="/images/test2.png" alt="image description" /></p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="jekyll" /><category term="update" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[]]></summary></entry></feed>